{"word":"εἰκών","slug":"εἰκών","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>εἰϰών, όνος, ἡ</el></b> [the basic idea is resemblance to some other entity; <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pf.\">pf.</a> of Homeric <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:εἴκω\">εἴκω</a></el>: <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἔοικα\">ἔοικα</a></el>] ‘<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ someth.\">someth.</a> that bears a likeness to <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ someth.\">someth.</a> else’, <b>image, likeness<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> a crafted object <b><a href='B:470 22:20'>Mt 22:20</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ par.\">par.</a>; <b><a href='B:520 1:23'>Ro 1:23</a>; <a href='B:730 13:14'>Rv 13:14f</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ freq.\">freq.</a> in Rv. <b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> by extension, of non-crafted entities <b><a href='B:530 11:7'>1 Cor 11:7</a>; <a href='B:530 15:49'>15:49</a>; <a href='B:540 3:18'>2 Cor 3:18</a>; <a href='B:540 4:4'>4:4</a>; <a href='B:580 1:15'>Col 1:15</a>.</b> Equivalent to a model for character<b> <a href='B:520 8:29'>Ro 8:29</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:εἴκω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:εἵλατο\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}